        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8778",
        "content": "\"But I never lent either before.\"--He was turning over the leaves as he spoke.--\"The passage,\" he went on, \"besides for its own worth, is precious to me as showing how, through all his madness, his thoughts haunted the gates of wisdom.--Ah! here it is!",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "very low",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "very low"
